# Security guidelines

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/security.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/security.md) — a single source of truth shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift. It extends the universal security items (injection, exec sinks, randomness, secrets); it does not replace them.

Read and follow `coding-rules/rules/security.md` for all work in this repository: never log secrets or personal data, authorization checked server-side against the specific resource instance at every entry point, fail closed on check errors, least-privilege credentials and scopes, adaptive password hashing, and automated dependency audits.
